        "title": "fix(update): detect nested macOS gateway ancestry",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Walk the macOS process parent chain with `ps` so nested updater children inherit the existing gateway-ancestry block before package updates stop the managed Gateway service.\n- Thread the caller spawn timeout through macOS ancestry probes so restart polling keeps its 400ms probe budget.\n- Add regression coverage for the nested macOS updater path, timeout plumbing, and the changelog entry.\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/85120.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs CHANGELOG.md src/infra/restart-stale-pids.ts src/infra/restart-stale-pids.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 CHANGELOG.md src/infra/restart-stale-pids.ts src/infra/restart-stale-pids.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/restart-stale-pids.test.ts src/cli/update-cli.test.ts -- -t \"ancestor|gateway process tree|managed gateway service|poll timeout|caller timeout\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/restart-stale-pids.test.ts`\n\nBlocked validation:\n\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 pnpm check:changed` could not run here because local pnpm attempted a dependency repair/install before invoking the script. The direct Testbox wrapper path then failed because this shell is not authenticated with Blacksmith (`blacksmith auth login` required).\n- Live Crabbox mac proof is blocked in this shell: Crabbox has no coordinator/broker configured, and the configured Hetzner provider has no token.",
